SIMPLE: interloper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interloper
<hw>In"ter*lo`per</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>inter-</ets> + D. <ets>looper</ets> a runner, fr. <ets>loopen</ets>
to run; akin to E. <ets>leap</ets>. See <er>Leap</er>, and cf.
<er>Elope</er>.]</ety> <def>One who interlopes; one who unlawfully
intrudes upon a property, a station, or an office; one who interferes
wrongfully or officiously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The untrained man, . . . the <qex>interloper</qex> as to the
professions.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interlucate</ent>⟦br⟧
